WEBVTT

00:10.170 --> 00:12.846
_

00:12.894 --> 00:16.306
_

00:16.308 --> 00:20.272
_

00:20.338 --> 00:21.939
- Max, snow day!
- Yeah.

00:21.973 --> 00:23.307
Heck yeah, snow day.

00:23.341 --> 00:24.975
I mean, technically it's snow evening,

00:25.010 --> 00:26.310
but that kinda
lacks poetry don't you think?

00:26.344 --> 00:27.706
- Sure.
- There's nothing quite like

00:27.740 --> 00:29.472
the sheer magic of the words, "snow day."

00:29.506 --> 00:30.514
- Yeah.
- Say it with me.

00:30.549 --> 00:32.249
Yeah, maybe later,
cause right now I gotta get

00:32.284 --> 00:34.418
this hospital ready for
the worst storm that we've seen

00:34.452 --> 00:35.920
in I don't know how many years.

00:35.954 --> 00:37.988
72 years. Yeah, it's a long time.

00:38.023 --> 00:40.524
But, uh, you know,
we had comparable snowfalls

00:40.559 --> 00:43.994
back in 2010 and 2016 but this
one's gonna be a lot more like

00:44.029 --> 00:46.931
- the great blizzard of 1947.
- Why do you know all this?

00:46.965 --> 00:48.599
Well, you know,
I have a passion for weather.

00:48.633 --> 00:50.301
Check this out. Look.
I put an anemometer on the roof

00:50.335 --> 00:51.468
seven years ago and
it remains the best decision

00:51.503 --> 00:53.270
I ever made in my life.

00:53.305 --> 00:54.939
Look. I mean, look at the
fluctuations in the storm.

00:54.973 --> 00:56.340
We can track it by its
geolocation, you know?

00:56.374 --> 00:58.442
Oh, God. She is all over the place.

00:58.476 --> 01:00.277
That explains why half the hospitals

01:00.312 --> 01:01.712
in this city have shut down.

01:01.746 --> 01:03.681
Uh, can y'all take those...
go to oncology.

01:03.715 --> 01:05.983
- Thank you.
- Private hospitals are wimps.

01:06.017 --> 01:07.618
Public hospitals don't get snow days.

01:07.652 --> 01:10.221
Laura, can we turn the heat up
two degrees? Two degrees.

01:10.255 --> 01:12.289
Thank you. I stocked up
on food, meds, supplies.

01:12.324 --> 01:13.557
I discharged every patient
I safely could,

01:13.592 --> 01:15.326
and I pared down to a skeleton crew.

01:15.360 --> 01:17.027
Well, what about you?
You going home to Georgia?

01:17.062 --> 01:19.129
I convinced her to go
to her parents' house,

01:19.164 --> 01:21.465
where she'll be enduring
a much more judgmental

01:21.499 --> 01:22.566
- type of storm.
- Oh yeah, I get ya.

01:22.601 --> 01:24.068
Yeah.

01:24.102 --> 01:26.136
Looks like you got this amigo.

01:26.171 --> 01:28.472
Oh, you know, this isn't so bad.

01:28.506 --> 01:30.574
This is nothing.
The great white out of 1888,

01:30.609 --> 01:32.209
they had to shut down Maine.

01:32.244 --> 01:33.477
Literally closed it
like it was a Denny's.

01:33.511 --> 01:35.012
Safety first.

01:35.046 --> 01:37.003
Well, 400 people still died that day.

01:39.017 --> 01:40.651
But we will be fine.

01:40.685 --> 01:42.152
Move it!

01:42.187 --> 01:44.054
Snow day, Dora!

01:44.089 --> 01:45.189
Snow day! Look it!

01:45.223 --> 01:46.523
No, I hear you.

01:46.558 --> 01:48.092
Look, I've got this cool weather app.

01:53.475 --> 01:57.410
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

